  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Solidity seems to have trouble initializing a static array using a constant as a size. The following code produces solidity errors.\n\n```\nuint constant CELLS = 10;\n...\nfunction initmap()\n{\n      uint[CELLS]  memory map;\n     ... \n}\n```\n\nProduces: `Error: Invalid array length.`\n\nAdditionally, attempting to initialize an array in this fashion\n\n```\nfunction initmap()\n{\n      uint[]  memory map;\n      map.length = CELLS;\n     ... \n}\n```\n\nProduces : `Error: Expression has to be an lvalue.`\n",
